-- Average Price of African Tea Falls to $2.12 Per Kilogram at Mombasa Sale
-- Ana Monteiro
-- 2010-07-14T07:07:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-14/average-price-of-african-tea-falls-to-2-12-per-kilogram-at-mombasa-sale.html

          
          
             The average price of African tea
declined to $2.12 per kilogram (2.2 pounds) at the world’s
biggest sale of the leaves in Kenya’s port city of Mombasa.  
 The average price fell from $2.16 at the previous sale, Tea
Brokers East Africa Ltd. said in an e-mailed report from Mombasa
today.  
 The top grade of tea sold for as much as $3.80 per
kilogram, according to the report.  
          
          


  


        